The paper deals with fashion recommendation and uses deep learning techniques to learn compatibility relationships among fashion items. This involves processing visual and textual information, which suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories. However, given the focus on image processing and the use of LSTMs, it is most likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also involves learning a visual-semantic space, which suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques, which suggests that it could belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) or Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with fashion, which suggests that it could belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
